headline.main: M'ARTHUR'S ARMY AGAIN REPELS FOE; Captives Taken as Infiltration Effort Fails -- Japanese Air Units Virtually Inactive M'ARTHUR'S ARMY AGAIN REPELS FOE

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Jan. 31. -- The battered and diminished American-Filipino forces of General Douglas MacArthur again have hurled back and frustrated determined Japanese attempts to infiltrate their Bataan Peninsula lines, and have taken some prisoners as well.
